1
00:00:06,589 --> 00:00:08,842
<i>You have one new voice message.</i>

2
00:00:10,927 --> 00:00:12,554
<i>First message.</i>

3
00:00:12,637 --> 00:00:13,930
<i>Oh, hi there.</i>

4
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:16,266
<i>Uh, sorry,</i>
<i>but something… something came up,</i>

5
00:00:16,349 --> 00:00:18,393
<i>and I have to go into the office now.</i>

6
00:00:18,476 --> 00:00:20,854
<i>Uh, I'll have to cancel Reina's sleepover.</i>

7
00:00:20,937 --> 00:00:22,731
<i>I already let your mother know.</i>

8
00:00:23,231 --> 00:00:27,068
<i>Daddy, I don't wanna go home!</i>
<i>I wanna stay with you!</i>

9
00:00:27,569 --> 00:00:30,697
<i>Sorry, sweetheart.</i>
<i>We'll see each other again soon, okay?</i>

10
00:00:31,197 --> 00:00:34,701
<i>So I should be able to reschedule</i>
<i>for next weekend. I can make it then.</i>

11
00:00:35,326 --> 00:00:37,829
<i>Oh, by the way,</i>
<i>someone told me that Kazuko Hosoki</i>

12
00:00:37,912 --> 00:00:40,290
<i>used to have a yakuza boss</i>
<i>for a boyfriend.</i>

13
00:00:40,373 --> 00:00:41,875
<i>Is that true?</i>

14
00:00:41,958 --> 00:00:44,711
<i>I also heard that she spends</i>
<i>a lot of money at host clubs every night</i>

15
00:00:44,794 --> 00:00:46,838
<i>and surrounds herself with young guys</i>

16
00:00:46,921 --> 00:00:48,548
<i>like she's some kind of empress.</i>

17
00:00:48,631 --> 00:00:51,509
Don't talk about things like that
in front of our kid.

18
00:00:51,593 --> 00:00:54,220
<i>Daddy, I don't wanna go home!</i>

19
00:00:54,304 --> 00:00:57,265
<i>Look, Reina, why don't I buy you</i>
<i>that stuffed animal we saw, okay?</i>

20
00:00:57,348 --> 00:00:58,725
<i>Yay! Stuffed animal!</i>

21
00:00:58,808 --> 00:01:00,185
<i>Sorry. I'll be in touch.</i>

22
00:01:15,575 --> 00:01:17,827
I got married
right after my novel came out.

23
00:01:19,079 --> 00:01:22,624
After that, years went by,
and I struggled to release a second one.

24
00:01:24,834 --> 00:01:27,128
Then, when we decided to have a kid,

25
00:01:27,212 --> 00:01:30,757
he started forcing me into taking on
the role of a wife and mother.

26
00:01:33,134 --> 00:01:34,552
One day, while he was drunk,

27
00:01:35,386 --> 00:01:39,182
he said to me, "No one is waiting
for your next novel anymore, you know?"

28
00:01:41,601 --> 00:01:43,311
It basically crushed me.

29
00:01:43,853 --> 00:01:45,105
But then Reina…

30
00:01:46,397 --> 00:01:47,524
That's my daughter.

31
00:01:48,441 --> 00:01:50,819
She'd already learned to read quite a bit.

32
00:01:51,736 --> 00:01:54,364
And I walked in on her
trying to read my book.

33
00:01:56,074 --> 00:01:59,994
She couldn't possibly have understood it
because it's full of kanji,

34
00:02:01,037 --> 00:02:02,413
but she kept going and going,

35
00:02:02,497 --> 00:02:05,291
just reading the hiragana parts
she could catch.

36
00:02:07,710 --> 00:02:08,878
When I saw that,

37
00:02:10,421 --> 00:02:12,674
I told myself to release a second book.

38
00:02:14,717 --> 00:02:16,886
Even if nobody else is,

39
00:02:16,970 --> 00:02:19,139
at least my daughter
will be waiting for it.

40
00:02:20,181 --> 00:02:21,432
That's how I feel.

41
00:02:24,060 --> 00:02:25,103
Minori…

42
00:02:27,188 --> 00:02:28,940
I'm also waiting for it.

43
00:02:29,023 --> 00:02:30,567
I want to read your novel.

44
00:02:36,406 --> 00:02:38,992
Mm. So how did things end up
with Hotta-san?

45
00:02:41,911 --> 00:02:43,454
That man…

46
00:02:45,748 --> 00:02:47,709
He never tried to control me.

47
00:02:47,792 --> 00:02:49,752
He let me do my own thing.

48
00:02:51,171 --> 00:02:55,258
Our relationship was based on respect
for the other person's life.

49
00:02:55,341 --> 00:02:57,343
So you two never fought?

50
00:02:57,427 --> 00:02:59,304
Oh, of course we did.

51
00:02:59,929 --> 00:03:02,599
At one point,
things turned sour between us.

52
00:03:02,682 --> 00:03:06,769
Although… it wasn't a good time
for the country either.

53
00:03:07,270 --> 00:03:08,479
What do you mean?

54
00:03:08,563 --> 00:03:10,982
<i>It was the oil crisis.</i>

55
00:03:11,065 --> 00:03:14,027
<i>Prices skyrocketed,</i>
<i>and our lives changed completely.</i>

56
00:03:14,110 --> 00:03:15,445
<i>The government had to step in.</i>

57
00:03:16,029 --> 00:03:19,282
<i>They ordered businesses</i>
<i>to reduce hours to save electricity,</i>

58
00:03:19,365 --> 00:03:22,327
<i>so the streets ended up empty,</i>
<i>and so did my club.</i>

59
00:03:22,410 --> 00:03:25,121
<i>We were driven to the brink</i>
<i>in a very short time.</i>

60
00:03:25,205 --> 00:03:27,957
I'm so sorry
things have ended up like this.

61
00:03:28,458 --> 00:03:29,876
Here. I know it's not much,

62
00:03:29,959 --> 00:03:32,420
but you can take everyone out
for a nice meal.

63
00:03:32,503 --> 00:03:34,839
Please call us
if you ever need a band again.

64
00:03:34,923 --> 00:03:37,300
Thank you so much. I appreciate you all.

65
00:03:37,383 --> 00:03:38,426
All right. Let's go.

66
00:04:06,913 --> 00:04:08,998
Another slow day today.

67
00:04:09,082 --> 00:04:10,625
Maybe we should close early.

68
00:04:10,708 --> 00:04:12,168
Oh boy.

69
00:04:12,252 --> 00:04:15,129
If things keep going like this,
we'll go out of business.

70
00:04:15,213 --> 00:04:17,924
Whose idea was it
to reduce business hours anyway?

71
00:04:18,007 --> 00:04:20,218
I wonder how long they'll keep this up.

72
00:04:20,718 --> 00:04:22,095
Who knows?

73
00:04:25,390 --> 00:04:27,308
Oh. Hi, Noboru.

74
00:04:28,268 --> 00:04:29,936
What are you doing here alone?

75
00:04:30,019 --> 00:04:31,729
Did he send you here?

76
00:04:31,813 --> 00:04:32,647
Madam,

77
00:04:33,690 --> 00:04:34,857
can I talk to you?

78
00:04:47,161 --> 00:04:49,998
Go ahead and place your bets.
Go ahead. Place your bets.

79
00:04:50,081 --> 00:04:51,958
Go on. Go on. Place your bets, gentlemen.

80
00:04:52,041 --> 00:04:53,626
Place your bets. Place your bets.

81
00:04:53,710 --> 00:04:56,170
Are you ready? Are you ready?
Go ahead and place your bets.

82
00:04:56,254 --> 00:04:58,172
- Place your bets.
- Okay. Done.

83
00:05:00,008 --> 00:05:00,967
All set.

84
00:05:02,260 --> 00:05:03,177
Showdown.

85
00:05:06,764 --> 00:05:07,807
Middle card, three.

86
00:05:07,890 --> 00:05:10,393
Anyone with three, open it.
Open it if you have three.

87
00:05:11,060 --> 00:05:12,854
I'm gonna have to call it.

88
00:05:13,646 --> 00:05:15,356
Today just ain't my day.

89
00:05:16,691 --> 00:05:18,443
Isn't it a bit soon to give up?

90
00:05:19,444 --> 00:05:22,655
If you'd like, I could always spot you.

91
00:05:29,620 --> 00:05:31,372
Not in this economy.

92
00:05:31,456 --> 00:05:33,708
I'll come back soon.

93
00:05:34,959 --> 00:05:37,128
- I also better go.
- Yep.

94
00:05:37,211 --> 00:05:38,629
Yeah, same for me.

95
00:05:39,130 --> 00:05:41,341
- Thank you for the game.
- Yes, thank you.

96
00:05:53,561 --> 00:05:57,231
You know it's bad for business
when the yakuza can't afford to gamble.

97
00:05:58,649 --> 00:06:02,862
My club's doing badly enough.
Are you managing your family all right?

98
00:06:04,447 --> 00:06:06,115
You don't need to worry about it.

99
00:06:07,367 --> 00:06:10,036
I know you're trying to save face,

100
00:06:10,119 --> 00:06:12,121
but if you need it,
I can get you some money.

101
00:06:13,289 --> 00:06:17,210
Living off the money a woman gives you
is exactly how you lose face.

102
00:06:23,216 --> 00:06:26,135
Hey. What if I sell the rights to my club?

103
00:06:26,928 --> 00:06:28,763
Business isn't doing well anyway,

104
00:06:28,846 --> 00:06:31,349
but it should be enough
to get you through for now.

105
00:06:32,308 --> 00:06:34,310
You're the one who got it back for me,
you know.

106
00:06:34,811 --> 00:06:36,562
- If it can be of help to you--
- That's enough.

107
00:06:41,317 --> 00:06:42,443
Hmm.

108
00:06:45,071 --> 00:06:47,115
My business is none of your concern.

109
00:06:47,198 --> 00:06:48,157
Yes, but…

110
00:06:50,785 --> 00:06:54,080
I know you need money
to keep the newer members afloat though.

111
00:06:54,705 --> 00:06:57,041
Let me at least
take care of their allowances.

112
00:07:03,965 --> 00:07:05,383
I'm very sorry.

113
00:07:22,567 --> 00:07:23,443
Thanks.

114
00:07:24,026 --> 00:07:25,445
Call me up anytime.

115
00:07:44,297 --> 00:07:46,382
I hope you know what you've just done.

116
00:07:58,478 --> 00:07:59,812
You little shit.

117
00:08:00,438 --> 00:08:03,316
Now you're gonna find out
what happens when you play with meth.

118
00:08:05,526 --> 00:08:07,069
Please! Have mercy!

119
00:08:08,321 --> 00:08:12,033
My dad's factory went under,
and I needed money!

120
00:08:13,284 --> 00:08:15,786
I'm the only one making money at home.

121
00:08:15,870 --> 00:08:17,330
I had no choice!

122
00:08:19,165 --> 00:08:21,709
You're a disgrace
to the Edogawa-ikka family!

123
00:08:23,503 --> 00:08:24,337
Hey.

124
00:08:25,087 --> 00:08:26,172
Yes, boss.

125
00:08:33,513 --> 00:08:35,223
How'd you get the meth, huh?

126
00:08:36,974 --> 00:08:38,809
Where'd you even get the money for that?

127
00:08:47,693 --> 00:08:48,945
Answer.

128
00:09:08,214 --> 00:09:09,799
Who was it, Noboru?

129
00:09:11,551 --> 00:09:13,052
Who gave you the money?

130
00:09:19,725 --> 00:09:21,102
Thank you for coming.

131
00:09:22,937 --> 00:09:24,063
Mm.

132
00:09:24,146 --> 00:09:27,608
It must be hard to do business
when the streets are empty like this.

133
00:09:27,692 --> 00:09:29,569
Yes, it truly is.

134
00:09:40,413 --> 00:09:42,540
What are you doing here? You didn't call.

135
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:45,501
I'm closing up.
Do you wanna go grab a drink somewhere?

136
00:09:46,836 --> 00:09:48,546
Noboru has been expelled.

137
00:09:49,046 --> 00:09:50,756
What? Why?

138
00:09:53,384 --> 00:09:55,428
He used the money that you gave him

139
00:09:56,345 --> 00:09:57,597
to start dealing meth.

140
00:09:59,557 --> 00:10:00,975
Oh no.

141
00:10:01,684 --> 00:10:04,395
He told you the young members
were struggling to get by

142
00:10:04,478 --> 00:10:06,939
and asked you for money behind my back,
didn't he?

143
00:10:12,111 --> 00:10:13,904
Yakuza are the kind of people

144
00:10:13,988 --> 00:10:16,991
who'd rather deceive everyone else
before we get deceived.

145
00:10:17,658 --> 00:10:19,619
If someone shows us sympathy,

146
00:10:20,119 --> 00:10:23,122
we take advantage and bleed them dry.
That's just how we are.

147
00:10:28,836 --> 00:10:31,339
That's why I told you
not to get involved in what we do.

148
00:10:34,759 --> 00:10:37,178
I just wanted to help you. That's all.

149
00:10:39,555 --> 00:10:41,932
Because I'm the only person
who can do that.

150
00:10:43,768 --> 00:10:45,186
I never asked for your help.

151
00:10:50,107 --> 00:10:51,901
Don't come around for a while.

152
00:11:34,402 --> 00:11:36,737
FORTUNE-TELLING

153
00:11:50,501 --> 00:11:52,086
MASAYA HOTTA

154
00:11:52,169 --> 00:11:53,379
KAZUKO HOSOKI

155
00:11:56,132 --> 00:11:57,883
Would you like to hear the results?

156
00:11:58,926 --> 00:12:00,177
Yes, please.

157
00:12:01,429 --> 00:12:05,766
You and this man
share excellent compatibility.

158
00:12:06,267 --> 00:12:07,727
You sure about that?

159
00:12:07,810 --> 00:12:09,937
Yes. It's very rare to see.

160
00:12:11,188 --> 00:12:14,608
But having too much compatibility
isn't good either.

161
00:12:14,692 --> 00:12:18,154
When you're in a lucky phase,
you amplify each other,

162
00:12:18,237 --> 00:12:21,115
but the same thing happens
when you're in a bad place.

163
00:12:21,615 --> 00:12:23,617
For you, especially.

164
00:12:24,744 --> 00:12:27,705
You're the type of person
who drags everyone along with you

165
00:12:27,788 --> 00:12:29,749
when you hit a streak of bad luck.

166
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:33,002
About ten years ago…

167
00:12:35,588 --> 00:12:38,299
you lost someone close to you, didn't you?

168
00:12:38,966 --> 00:12:41,552
Yes, my mother passed away.

169
00:12:43,554 --> 00:12:44,722
I imagine

170
00:12:45,931 --> 00:12:49,226
that since you were little,
you've never been able to sit still.

171
00:12:49,810 --> 00:12:50,853
That's true.

172
00:12:51,520 --> 00:12:53,230
You have more energy inside of you

173
00:12:53,314 --> 00:12:56,233
than most people
ever experience in their lives.

174
00:12:56,817 --> 00:13:00,821
An abundance of energy
that you simply cannot contain.

175
00:13:00,905 --> 00:13:04,158
This is why you've been working so hard
without a break for so long.

176
00:13:06,368 --> 00:13:10,581
You're a single-minded person,
and you stick to your own ideas.

177
00:13:11,248 --> 00:13:14,960
But people have taken advantage of you
when you least expected it,

178
00:13:15,044 --> 00:13:17,963
and you've gone through
many hardships because of that.

179
00:13:19,381 --> 00:13:23,260
Despite that,
you've fallen and gotten back up.

180
00:13:23,344 --> 00:13:25,304
Over and over again.

181
00:13:27,264 --> 00:13:31,143
You've worked hard to get
where you are now, and it's paid off.

182
00:13:32,728 --> 00:13:33,771
How do you…

183
00:13:36,232 --> 00:13:40,861
Uh, how is it
that… that you know so much about me?

184
00:13:40,945 --> 00:13:43,781
My fortune-telling is based on statistics.

185
00:13:45,241 --> 00:13:47,409
Things become clear
through deciphering the records

186
00:13:47,493 --> 00:13:50,913
that have been accumulated over millennia
by my predecessors.

187
00:13:51,664 --> 00:13:53,249
Incredible.

188
00:13:54,083 --> 00:13:57,002
Is there anything else
that you want to ask me?

189
00:13:57,086 --> 00:13:58,170
Yes.

190
00:13:58,254 --> 00:14:00,756
Uh, when will my luck get better?

191
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:02,091
Right now.

192
00:14:02,174 --> 00:14:03,300
What do you mean?

193
00:14:03,801 --> 00:14:06,178
Your luck will improve
from this moment forward.

194
00:14:07,721 --> 00:14:12,434
The very fact that you passed by me once
but returned again,

195
00:14:12,518 --> 00:14:13,894
well, that proves it.

196
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:15,688
Right now?

197
00:14:17,273 --> 00:14:20,317
My findings suggest that you might
want to start a new business.

198
00:14:20,401 --> 00:14:22,862
I should start a new business?

199
00:14:27,533 --> 00:14:31,996
<i>You were in what is known</i>
<i>as a "Void Period," a period of bad luck.</i>

200
00:14:32,079 --> 00:14:33,664
<i>You're coming out of it now,</i>

201
00:14:34,164 --> 00:14:38,168
<i>and you have a chance to change</i>
<i>your line of work and try something new.</i>

202
00:14:58,355 --> 00:15:00,566
It's time to make a change around here.

203
00:15:01,066 --> 00:15:03,068
I'm turning this place into a disco.

204
00:15:03,152 --> 00:15:04,320
That's exciting.

205
00:15:04,403 --> 00:15:06,655
We're gonna make it
the number one disco in Tokyo.

206
00:15:06,739 --> 00:15:07,948
- Yes, ma'am.
- All right!

207
00:15:08,032 --> 00:15:09,116
All right, everyone.

208
00:15:09,199 --> 00:15:12,620
We need to replace the flooring first,
so let's start with the tables and chairs.

209
00:15:12,703 --> 00:15:13,996
Let's get everything outside.

210
00:15:14,496 --> 00:15:16,832
- Yes, sir.
- I need everyone to work hard.

211
00:15:16,916 --> 00:15:17,791
Yes, sir.

212
00:15:17,875 --> 00:15:19,752
We'll be very generous with your bonuses.

213
00:15:19,835 --> 00:15:21,128
- Take this.
- I got it.

214
00:15:21,211 --> 00:15:23,339
Hi, we're Disco Manhattan. Here you go.

215
00:15:23,422 --> 00:15:24,757
Please take one.

216
00:15:24,840 --> 00:15:26,884
Hi, we're Disco Manhattan.
Please take one.

217
00:15:26,967 --> 00:15:29,970
Disco Manhattan opening soon!
Here you go. Please take one!

218
00:15:30,054 --> 00:15:32,431
All the equipment
should be set up onstage, please.

219
00:15:33,432 --> 00:15:34,725
Hey, sis!

220
00:15:34,808 --> 00:15:37,811
I got the new flyers ready.
So which one do you think is better?

221
00:15:37,895 --> 00:15:39,772
Disco Manhattan. Here you go.

222
00:15:40,856 --> 00:15:43,317
We're Disco Manhattan.
Please take one. Please?

223
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:45,527
Disco Manhattan, opening soon!
Please take one.

224
00:15:45,611 --> 00:15:46,654
Hello, ma'am.

225
00:15:47,780 --> 00:15:48,739
Teppei.

226
00:15:48,822 --> 00:15:52,493
Nobody's gonna take a flyer from you
if you keep being polite like that.

227
00:15:53,702 --> 00:15:55,287
We'll show you how it's done.

228
00:15:55,371 --> 00:15:58,749
Oh, wait, but aren't you gonna
get into trouble with him?

229
00:16:00,542 --> 00:16:03,295
He's the one who told us to come.
He wanted to help you out.

230
00:16:03,379 --> 00:16:05,881
- Disco Manhattan is opening soon!
- Hey, guys. Here you go.

231
00:16:05,965 --> 00:16:08,133
- A new disco's opening.
- Opening soon!

232
00:16:08,217 --> 00:16:10,135
Thank you so much! Please, have one.

233
00:16:10,219 --> 00:16:13,263
Disco Manhattan is opening soon!
Here, take a flyer.

234
00:16:13,347 --> 00:16:15,891
Ladies, ladies, ladies, ladies!
Please, at least take one of these!

235
00:16:15,975 --> 00:16:19,561
You can throw it away later!
Ah, wonderful! Thank you!

236
00:16:25,275 --> 00:16:29,822
<i>Cards are bound to break me</i>
<i>But I ain't busted yet</i>

237
00:16:29,905 --> 00:16:33,701
<i>'Cause I've been called a natural lover</i>
<i>By that lady over there</i>

238
00:16:33,784 --> 00:16:37,871
<i>Honey, I'm just a natural gambler</i>
<i>But I try to do my share</i>

239
00:16:37,955 --> 00:16:40,040
<i>Go down gamblin'</i>

240
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:45,129
<i>Say it when you're runnin' low</i>

241
00:16:47,047 --> 00:16:49,508
<i>Go down gamblin'</i>

242
00:16:50,676 --> 00:16:54,179
<i>You may never have to go, no, no, no…</i>

243
00:17:09,695 --> 00:17:11,613
- Thank you.
- Here you go. 500 yen.

244
00:17:35,679 --> 00:17:38,015
<i>My new business is a huge success.</i>

245
00:17:38,098 --> 00:17:39,516
<i>Just like your prediction said.</i>

246
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:43,187
You told me my luck would improve,
and you were completely right.

247
00:17:44,104 --> 00:17:45,898
The success of your disco club

248
00:17:45,981 --> 00:17:50,360
is simply the result of your determination
and your hard work.

249
00:17:52,321 --> 00:17:54,239
The only thing I did
was to give you advice

250
00:17:54,323 --> 00:17:56,658
based on ancient divination techniques.

251
00:17:56,742 --> 00:17:59,745
I would love you
to continue giving me advice.

252
00:17:59,828 --> 00:18:03,999
Oh, I brought you a small token of thanks.

253
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:06,043
I appreciate the offer,

254
00:18:06,126 --> 00:18:08,253
but you've already paid me
for my readings.

255
00:18:08,337 --> 00:18:10,422
Oh, please, take it anyway.

256
00:18:10,506 --> 00:18:12,841
I don't accept anyone's gifts

257
00:18:12,925 --> 00:18:16,512
because that might disrupt
the flow of my divinations.

258
00:18:16,595 --> 00:18:17,846
Oh.

259
00:18:18,889 --> 00:18:22,184
I had no idea
fortune tellers were so ascetic.

260
00:18:23,143 --> 00:18:25,896
You know, I don't think
that I could ever live like that.

261
00:18:26,396 --> 00:18:29,274
<i>You may never have to go, no</i>

262
00:19:08,647 --> 00:19:10,274
Looks like business is good.

263
00:19:11,108 --> 00:19:13,819
It's thanks to Teppei
and the others helping us.

264
00:19:15,237 --> 00:19:18,323
Yes, well,
they just wanted extra pocket money.

265
00:19:19,324 --> 00:19:21,076
Don't be too grateful to them.

266
00:19:23,871 --> 00:19:25,247
Oh! You know what?

267
00:19:25,330 --> 00:19:29,084
A fortune teller told me
that you and I were made for each other,

268
00:19:29,168 --> 00:19:31,879
and that our luck
will keep getting better from now on.

269
00:19:31,962 --> 00:19:33,964
Oh really?

270
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:37,092
Didn't you say
you didn't believe in all that stuff?

271
00:19:37,176 --> 00:19:38,969
Really? Did I?

272
00:19:44,099 --> 00:19:45,601
So, do you wanna

273
00:19:46,226 --> 00:19:47,519
go for a drink somewhere?

274
00:19:48,896 --> 00:19:49,897
Mm-hmm.

275
00:20:09,791 --> 00:20:11,043
Hotta!

276
00:20:22,221 --> 00:20:23,847
What the hell do you want?

277
00:20:25,098 --> 00:20:28,227
Looks like
you're a real big shot now, huh?

278
00:20:30,604 --> 00:20:32,481
Takiguchi-san,

279
00:20:33,690 --> 00:20:37,319
I wish that… I could say the same for you.

280
00:20:40,489 --> 00:20:42,783
That's 'cause somebody set me up!

281
00:20:45,577 --> 00:20:47,204
Get out of here now!

282
00:20:49,790 --> 00:20:52,209
I don't have anywhere to go.

283
00:21:04,054 --> 00:21:05,180
Hotta!

284
00:21:17,943 --> 00:21:18,902
No!

285
00:21:19,653 --> 00:21:22,406
Help! Somebody help!

286
00:21:24,866 --> 00:21:27,369
No, my love! Hang on! Hang on!

287
00:21:29,621 --> 00:21:31,456
Please don't leave me!

288
00:21:33,041 --> 00:21:34,960
Hotta! My love!

289
00:21:35,627 --> 00:21:37,921
Please stay with me!

290
00:21:38,005 --> 00:21:39,131
Please!

291
00:21:44,720 --> 00:21:46,680
SURGERY IN SESSION

292
00:22:30,015 --> 00:22:32,476
You'll be glad to know
the surgery was a success.

293
00:22:32,976 --> 00:22:34,353
He's going to be okay.

294
00:22:35,520 --> 00:22:37,481
Thank you so much, Doctor.

295
00:23:12,933 --> 00:23:13,892
Well…

296
00:23:16,645 --> 00:23:19,189
looks like
that fortune teller was wrong, huh?

297
00:23:22,776 --> 00:23:25,946
I dunno. You took four bullets,
and you're still alive.

298
00:23:26,029 --> 00:23:27,823
I would say that's pretty lucky.

299
00:23:35,580 --> 00:23:37,666
Oh. Are you all right?

300
00:23:41,211 --> 00:23:43,880
Uh, goddammit.

301
00:23:45,924 --> 00:23:47,634
Being with you

302
00:23:48,552 --> 00:23:50,429
is always exciting.

303
00:23:55,767 --> 00:23:57,644
So I've made a decision.

304
00:23:59,146 --> 00:24:01,064
I'm gonna stick with you forever.

305
00:24:05,652 --> 00:24:07,237
When you're an outlaw,

306
00:24:08,989 --> 00:24:11,074
you never know when you're gonna die.

307
00:24:13,160 --> 00:24:13,994
So…

308
00:24:15,996 --> 00:24:17,956
I won't be able to marry you.

309
00:24:19,416 --> 00:24:20,876
Are you okay with that?

310
00:24:24,337 --> 00:24:26,506
You know
I don't care about things like that.

311
00:24:28,216 --> 00:24:30,093
I would even follow you to hell.

312
00:25:07,464 --> 00:25:09,007
Isn't that kid adorable?

313
00:25:09,591 --> 00:25:13,094
No. Kids are only adorable
when they're in pictures.

314
00:25:20,560 --> 00:25:21,728
What is it?

315
00:25:24,940 --> 00:25:27,400
Wait a second,
you're not blushing, are you?

316
00:25:29,361 --> 00:25:30,403
Thank you both for waiting.

317
00:25:30,487 --> 00:25:32,447
Of course. Shall we go in?

318
00:25:35,116 --> 00:25:36,576
Uh, I dunno.

319
00:25:36,660 --> 00:25:39,663
- I'm not really a picture kind of guy.
- Come on now.

320
00:25:39,746 --> 00:25:41,831
- All right, ma'am. Please sit here.
- Okay.

321
00:25:43,333 --> 00:25:45,460
Sir, if you would. A little closer.

322
00:25:48,421 --> 00:25:51,091
Next time we come here,
we might have a baby with us.

323
00:25:51,174 --> 00:25:53,176
Hmm. I can't hear you.

324
00:25:55,470 --> 00:25:56,930
All right, here we go.

325
00:26:03,979 --> 00:26:06,523
You know,
the two of you would have a cute child.

326
00:26:18,952 --> 00:26:20,787
But there was no next time.

327
00:26:22,289 --> 00:26:25,375
This was the only photo
I ever took with Hotta.

328
00:26:26,418 --> 00:26:28,086
Do you mean that you broke up?

329
00:26:30,672 --> 00:26:31,798
Why?

330
00:26:32,340 --> 00:26:34,342
Didn't you wanna be with him forever?

331
00:26:36,469 --> 00:26:39,723
It's never that simple
between a man and a woman.

332
00:26:41,725 --> 00:26:43,977
I got most of the things I wanted,

333
00:26:44,769 --> 00:26:46,313
except for a child.

334
00:26:50,900 --> 00:26:55,196
Lately, I've been looking forward
to our conversations.

335
00:26:56,323 --> 00:26:59,492
It sort of feels like I'm telling
my daughter about my younger days.

336
00:26:59,576 --> 00:27:01,411
Me? Your daughter?

337
00:27:01,494 --> 00:27:03,038
What? Is that strange for you?

338
00:27:03,121 --> 00:27:05,707
Oh, not at all! Please go on.

339
00:27:08,001 --> 00:27:10,879
You'd better go home for today.
Your daughter must be waiting.

340
00:27:28,438 --> 00:27:31,399
This should be enough.
I've made a lot. Huh?

341
00:27:31,483 --> 00:27:32,859
- Yeah.
- The origami, right?

342
00:27:34,486 --> 00:27:36,196
- Good.
- I'm home.

343
00:27:36,279 --> 00:27:37,906
Welcome home.

344
00:27:39,449 --> 00:27:40,450
I'm sorry, Reina.

345
00:27:40,533 --> 00:27:42,202
Should I make deep-fried prawns
for dinner?

346
00:27:42,285 --> 00:27:44,412
- Yeah.
- Hear that? Deep-fried prawns.

347
00:27:44,496 --> 00:27:45,538
What's that?

348
00:27:46,039 --> 00:27:47,457
This is Shiro.

349
00:27:48,083 --> 00:27:49,876
Daddy bought it for me.

350
00:27:49,959 --> 00:27:52,962
- Yes, he bought it for you. It's Shiro.
- Mm-hmm.

351
00:27:55,757 --> 00:27:58,468
Yay! Yummy big prawns!
You can do it, Mommy!

352
00:27:58,551 --> 00:28:00,095
Careful now, honey. It's dangerous.

353
00:28:00,178 --> 00:28:02,013
- Why are you using chopsticks?
- What? Who cares?

354
00:28:02,097 --> 00:28:04,474
- Use your hand. It's dangerous, okay?
- That's way too scary.

355
00:28:04,557 --> 00:28:05,433
You can do it, Mommy!

356
00:28:05,517 --> 00:28:07,727
The Fire Bamboo Star is coming up next,

357
00:28:07,811 --> 00:28:09,479
which is the "Star of Change."

358
00:28:09,562 --> 00:28:13,400
It says
it's "perfect for starting something new."

359
00:28:13,483 --> 00:28:16,736
Well, then, maybe I should take up
ballroom dancing or something, hmm?

360
00:28:16,820 --> 00:28:18,613
- Sure, why not? Mm-hmm.
- Think I should? Huh?

361
00:28:18,697 --> 00:28:19,823
- Mmm.
- Mmm.

362
00:28:19,906 --> 00:28:21,241
Don't forget your veggies.

363
00:28:23,118 --> 00:28:24,411
Mmm!

364
00:28:26,371 --> 00:28:27,455
Here, Shiro.

365
00:28:27,539 --> 00:28:28,957
He can't eat that.

366
00:28:29,040 --> 00:28:31,209
- Eat it, Shiro.
- Shouldn't you eat that?

367
00:28:32,877 --> 00:28:33,920
Okay, I'll eat it.

368
00:28:34,003 --> 00:28:36,840
- Hey!
- That's a good girl! Way to go!

369
00:28:36,923 --> 00:28:38,967
<i>Down came the sun</i>

370
00:28:39,050 --> 00:28:40,760
<i>And dried up all the rain</i>

371
00:28:40,844 --> 00:28:42,971
<i>And the itsy-bitsy spider…</i>

372
00:28:43,054 --> 00:28:44,764
Oh, that's good. Hold on.

373
00:28:44,848 --> 00:28:46,433
- Here. We'll start again, okay?
- Okay.

374
00:28:46,516 --> 00:28:48,685
You should look at the audience.
Okay, let's go.

375
00:28:48,768 --> 00:28:52,605
<i>Itsy-bitsy spider</i>
<i>Went up the water spout</i>

376
00:28:52,689 --> 00:28:53,523
Yeah!

377
00:28:53,606 --> 00:28:57,569
<i>Down came the rain</i>
<i>And washed the spider out</i>

378
00:29:22,510 --> 00:29:27,140
HERE ARE SOME REFERENCE MATERIALS
ON CHIYOKO SHIMAKURA. -KAWATANI

379
00:29:42,489 --> 00:29:47,869
CHIYOKO SHIMAKURA TRICKED INTO
400-MILLION-YEN DEBT BY BOYFRIEND

380
00:30:16,064 --> 00:30:17,732
<i>Chiyoko Shimakura.</i>

381
00:30:18,900 --> 00:30:21,110
<i>One of Japan's most beloved singers.</i>

382
00:30:21,194 --> 00:30:24,531
<i>Her name shines brightly</i>
<i>in the history of Japanese entertainment.</i>

383
00:30:26,533 --> 00:30:27,700
<i>Her voice,</i>

384
00:30:28,201 --> 00:30:31,454
<i>beautiful and crystal-clear</i>
<i>as a bell ringing out,</i>

385
00:30:31,538 --> 00:30:34,707
<i>she captivated the hearts</i>
<i>of her fans throughout the country.</i>

386
00:30:49,514 --> 00:30:51,474
Thank you all very much.

387
00:30:51,558 --> 00:30:53,226
Wonderful job, everyone.

388
00:30:55,144 --> 00:30:56,271
Excuse me.

389
00:30:56,813 --> 00:30:58,606
Shimakura-san!

390
00:30:58,690 --> 00:31:00,483
Excuse me! Excuse me, sorry.

391
00:31:01,359 --> 00:31:03,820
Huh? Sawamura-san, what is it?
You look panicked.

392
00:31:03,903 --> 00:31:05,738
It's the debt collectors!

393
00:31:07,198 --> 00:31:08,032
What?

394
00:31:19,752 --> 00:31:21,170
You'll never get away with this!

395
00:31:21,254 --> 00:31:24,007
If your boyfriend tricked you,
you're still to blame for being gullible!

396
00:31:24,090 --> 00:31:27,176
That's right! Now that he's disappeared,
you're the one to pay!

397
00:31:27,260 --> 00:31:31,806
<i>In 1977, when Chiyoko Shimakura</i>
<i>was at the height of her fame,</i>

398
00:31:31,890 --> 00:31:34,392
<i>she was hit with an unexpected scandal.</i>

399
00:31:34,475 --> 00:31:36,436
Almost there, Shimakura-san!

400
00:31:36,519 --> 00:31:38,313
Oh no!
They're in front of the apartment too!

401
00:31:38,396 --> 00:31:41,316
- Guys, she's coming!
- Duck your head, hurry!

402
00:31:41,399 --> 00:31:44,777
<i>Her boyfriend had tricked her</i>
<i>into endorsing multiple promissory notes.</i>

403
00:31:44,861 --> 00:31:46,029
Pay what you owe!

404
00:31:46,112 --> 00:31:48,448
<i>And then one day, he disappeared,</i>

405
00:31:48,531 --> 00:31:52,452
<i>and she found herself saddled</i>
<i>with a debt of 430 million yen.</i>

406
00:31:59,042 --> 00:32:00,084
<i>One night,</i>

407
00:32:00,168 --> 00:32:03,421
<i>just as Chioyoko Shimakura</i>
<i>was in the throes of hell,</i>

408
00:32:03,922 --> 00:32:06,215
<i>she had a fateful encounter</i>

409
00:32:06,799 --> 00:32:08,760
<i>with Kazuko Hosoki.</i>

410
00:32:33,618 --> 00:32:34,494
Hey.

411
00:32:37,497 --> 00:32:38,456
Hey there.

412
00:32:39,582 --> 00:32:41,000
Are you okay?

413
00:32:43,711 --> 00:32:44,545
Don't do it.

414
00:32:52,220 --> 00:32:53,054
Aren't you…

415
00:32:55,181 --> 00:32:56,891
Chiyoko Shimakura?

416
00:32:59,936 --> 00:33:04,524
I can't believe a star as great as you
could get tricked by a man.

417
00:33:05,024 --> 00:33:08,611
How much longer is your run
at the Koma Theater going for?

418
00:33:12,156 --> 00:33:14,200
Two… two more weeks.

419
00:33:15,201 --> 00:33:17,203
Oh God. Two weeks?

420
00:33:18,538 --> 00:33:21,457
You'll just have to do your best
to try and get through it.

421
00:33:24,794 --> 00:33:26,838
How do you expect me to do that?

422
00:33:28,548 --> 00:33:31,509
I can hardly even sing anymore,
the way things are.

423
00:33:32,802 --> 00:33:34,846
And if I can't sing,
then I don't deserve to live.

424
00:33:36,723 --> 00:33:37,640
I should

425
00:33:39,058 --> 00:33:40,143
just get it over with.

426
00:33:40,226 --> 00:33:41,102
Stop that!

427
00:33:41,894 --> 00:33:44,147
You shouldn't talk about dying
so casually!

428
00:33:46,607 --> 00:33:49,110
Have you got any idea
how many people need you?

429
00:33:49,652 --> 00:33:51,487
Your music keeps them going!

430
00:34:01,789 --> 00:34:03,291
I'm gonna help you with this.

431
00:34:04,333 --> 00:34:05,668
Let me handle it.

432
00:34:08,046 --> 00:34:09,047
What?

433
00:34:09,672 --> 00:34:12,341
I'll help you
so that you can keep performing

434
00:34:12,425 --> 00:34:14,093
and complete your contract.

435
00:34:18,598 --> 00:34:21,017
There's no reason for you
to do that for me.

436
00:34:21,517 --> 00:34:25,146
I mean, we're… we're strangers.
We've only just met.

437
00:34:30,860 --> 00:34:32,403
I don't know about that.

438
00:34:33,654 --> 00:34:36,616
I was in the same position as you
a long time ago.

439
00:34:41,454 --> 00:34:44,165
You and I didn't meet here
just by chance, you know.

440
00:34:46,209 --> 00:34:47,919
This must have been fate.

441
00:35:21,536 --> 00:35:22,578
Please stay back!

442
00:35:26,457 --> 00:35:28,084
I'm Hotta, from Shinjuku.

443
00:35:29,710 --> 00:35:33,047
Starting today,
Chiyoko Shimakura will be under my care.

444
00:35:33,131 --> 00:35:35,216
- What?
- What's going on?

445
00:35:35,299 --> 00:35:38,761
If anyone has anything to say about it,
say it here. Right now.

446
00:35:40,847 --> 00:35:41,806
Well, if that's true…

447
00:35:41,889 --> 00:35:44,475
- Hotta-san.
- Come on, you can't do that to us.

448
00:35:49,897 --> 00:35:51,357
She can't get away with this.

449
00:35:51,440 --> 00:35:52,608
Out of the way, please.

450
00:35:59,448 --> 00:36:03,786
Chiyoko Shimakura will continue her run
of performances here at the Koma Theater,

451
00:36:04,453 --> 00:36:06,914
as she has many fans
who wanna hear her sing.

452
00:36:07,623 --> 00:36:09,125
After the final show,

453
00:36:09,208 --> 00:36:12,044
I'll set up a meeting with you all
to discuss everything.

454
00:36:12,879 --> 00:36:13,838
Excuse us.

455
00:36:51,000 --> 00:36:53,085
You look completely different.

456
00:36:54,545 --> 00:36:58,591
Except that I… I don't feel
confident enough to sing through the show.

457
00:36:58,674 --> 00:37:00,843
What do you mean, Ochiyo?

458
00:37:00,927 --> 00:37:03,596
You know
we're at the point of no return now.

459
00:37:04,597 --> 00:37:06,182
Mm. Yes, but…

460
00:37:07,975 --> 00:37:09,268
Shimakura-san.

461
00:37:09,769 --> 00:37:10,937
Places, please.

462
00:37:12,688 --> 00:37:14,732
This is it. Time for you to shine.

463
00:37:15,233 --> 00:37:16,108
Let's go.

464
00:37:19,612 --> 00:37:21,030
Listen, Ochiyo.

465
00:37:21,113 --> 00:37:23,908
You don't have to worry
about the debt collectors anymore.

466
00:37:23,991 --> 00:37:27,036
Right now, all you have to do
is focus on your singing.

467
00:37:31,082 --> 00:37:35,920
Uh, hey. What about the… the scary dream
I had last night, remember?

468
00:37:36,003 --> 00:37:38,089
Yeah, of course I do. What about it?

469
00:37:38,172 --> 00:37:39,632
It was my voice.

470
00:37:40,132 --> 00:37:42,176
My voice wouldn't come out.

471
00:37:42,260 --> 00:37:45,012
I'm onstage, and the curtains open,
and I open my mouth,

472
00:37:45,096 --> 00:37:47,890
but right when I try to sing,
nothing comes out.

473
00:37:47,974 --> 00:37:49,809
Don't worry about dreams like that.

474
00:37:49,892 --> 00:37:52,561
Just focus on singing
with all of your strength,

475
00:37:53,062 --> 00:37:55,815
and don't think about
that terrible man anymore.

476
00:37:56,774 --> 00:37:57,942
You'll be okay.

477
00:37:58,025 --> 00:38:01,404
You were prepared to die once already.
Now you can do anything.

478
00:38:08,953 --> 00:38:11,872
Oh God! Please! Tell me what to do!

479
00:38:11,956 --> 00:38:14,000
I'm so scared
that my voice won't come out!

480
00:38:14,083 --> 00:38:15,876
You'll make it come out no matter what.

481
00:38:16,627 --> 00:38:18,546
Never forget who you are.

482
00:38:19,130 --> 00:38:20,298
You're amazing.

483
00:38:20,840 --> 00:38:22,883
You are Chiyoko Shimakura!

484
00:39:18,814 --> 00:39:22,360
<i>All I have to offer you</i>

485
00:39:23,527 --> 00:39:27,281
<i>Is my love alone</i>

486
00:39:28,157 --> 00:39:32,745
<i>Yet you are always</i>

487
00:39:32,828 --> 00:39:37,458
<i>Yes, that's right, you're a cruel one</i>

488
00:39:37,541 --> 00:39:40,961
<i>With the tip of your little finger</i>

489
00:39:42,088 --> 00:39:45,216
<i>You reach out to my heart</i>

490
00:39:46,759 --> 00:39:51,305
<i>Yet today, once again</i>

491
00:39:51,389 --> 00:39:56,018
<i>You only give it a touch</i>

492
00:39:56,102 --> 00:40:00,648
<i>Even after the flowers fall</i>

493
00:40:00,731 --> 00:40:04,485
<i>These feelings of mine</i>

494
00:40:05,736 --> 00:40:09,698
<i>Of our heartrending love</i>

495
00:40:10,366 --> 00:40:14,203
<i>Will stay in my embrace</i>

496
00:40:14,995 --> 00:40:16,956
<i>They'll stay in my embrace</i>

497
00:40:17,039 --> 00:40:20,418
<i>This secret</i>

498
00:40:21,794 --> 00:40:25,131
<i>Will belong only to me</i>

499
00:40:26,173 --> 00:40:30,511
<i>This love that I offer you</i>

500
00:40:31,137 --> 00:40:35,641
<i>Is the kind that never fades away</i>

501
00:40:50,322 --> 00:40:51,824
<i>From that point on,</i>

502
00:40:51,907 --> 00:40:56,370
<i>Kazuko Hosoki and Chiyoko Shimakura</i>
<i>started a new journey together</i>

503
